  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Author of the Noctes Atticae, probably born in Rome between AD 125 and 130 (Gell. NA 7,6,12). The sparse information about his life that can be gleaned from 
    the work relates primarily to education and spiritual development..."</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1867, p. 235: "A. Gellius...a Latin grammarian,
    with regard to whose history we posses no source of information except his own book...His well known work entitled
    Noctes Atticae...is a sort of miscellany, containing numerous extracts from Greek and Roman writers, on a great variety of topics..""</mads:note>
